Arsenal have announced that they will be welcoming 2,000 fans to the Emirates, for their Europa League clash against Rapid Vienna on Thursday, December 3. This follows the UK Government’s announcement today, that London is located in a Tier 2 area under the latest Coronavirus guidelines. Gooners have not been able to physically watch their team for almost nine months A statement on the club’s official website read: “While we appreciate that reduced capacity matches will be far from being ‘back to normal’, we can’t wait to welcome our fans back home for what will be a historic moment for the club.” It added that “we will not be running a ticketing ballot for the match against Rapid Vienna. “For this match only, we will be running a “first come, first served” priority sale to Gold and Premium Members who made their Initial Payment and registered for the ballot in September.”